gov.nih.nlm.nls.lvg.Trie

Class TrieTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.nls.lvg.Trie.TrieTree

  • public class TrieTree
extends java.lang.Object
    This class creates an object of a trie tree. A trie trie include a tree structure consists of trie nodes.

      • LoadRulesFromFile

        public void LoadRulesFromFile(java.lang.String dir,
                              java.lang.String fName,
                              boolean reverse,
                              boolean duplicateFlag)
        Read in LVG trie rules from a specified rule.
        Parameters:
        dir - the path name of the directory of the LVG trie rule file
        fName - the file name of the LVG trie rule file
        reverse - true or false to load the rule in forward or backward
        duplicateFlag - flag to send warning message when duplicate rule direction from the file. All rules in LVG trie are bi-directional.

      • PrintTrie

        public void PrintTrie(boolean details,
                      boolean rulesFlag,
                      boolean exceptionFlag)
        Print the detail informatin of current trie tree.
        Parameters:
        details - true or false to print out details (traverse path) or not of the current trie tree
        rulesFlag - true or false to print out all rules of the current trie tree
        exceptionFlag - true or false to print out all exceptions of the current trie tree
